columns.name: Community District
columns.description: Community District which is represented by a two-letter borough code followed by a two-digit community district number

columns.name: District Currently Eligible for Service
columns.description: Whether or not the Community District is eligible for curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: District Currently Receiving Service
columns.description: Whether or not the Community District receives curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Total Number of Addresses in District
columns.description: The term "Addresses" is used to describe buildings as identified by unique BBL (Borough, Block, Lot). BBL is a unique ID assigned to each property in NYC and in some occasions a single BBL may technically be associated with multiple mailing addresses. Total Number of Addresses is the sum of BBLs within each district.

columns.name: Total Number of Households in District
columns.description: Sum of individual residential units (as classified in DCP's PLUTO and MapPLUTO databases) associated with Addresses/BBLs in each community district.

columns.name: Total Number of Interested Addresses
columns.description: Addresses that have expressed interest in curbside composting by signing up at nyc.gov/curbsidecomposting.

columns.name: Percent of Interested Addresses
columns.description: The percent of addresses interested in participating based on total number of addresses in the district.

columns.name: Total Number of Addresses Receiving Service
columns.description: Addresses that are currently getting curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Percent of Addresses Receiving Service
columns.description: The percent of addresses receiving curbside composting sign-up service based on the total number of addresses in the district.

columns.name: Total Number of Addresses Waiting to be Routed, Not Yet Receiving Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of addresses in the district, the percent of addresses waiting to be routed once their district is added for curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Percent of Addresses Waiting to be Routed, Not Yet Receiving Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of addresses in the district, the percent of addresses waiting to be routed once their district is added for curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Total Number of Addresses Not Yet Ready for Service
columns.description: Addresses that are in an eligible district but are not yet ready to be serviced because DSNY has not received: confirmation from building management, finalized bin set out location, and/or required information to service the address.

columns.name: Percent of Addresses Not Yet Ready for Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of addresses in the district, the percent of addresses not ready for service because DSNY has not received confirmation from building management, finalized bin set out location, and/or required information to service the address.

columns.name: Total Number of Interested Households
columns.description: Households (total residential units) associated with an address where at least one person has expressed interest in curbside composting by signing up at nyc.gov/curbsidecomposting

columns.name: Percent of Interested Households
columns.description: Based on the total number of households in a district, the percent that are interested in participating.

columns.name: Total Number Households Receiving Service
columns.description: Households that receive curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Percent of Households Receiving Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of households in a district, the percent that are receiving curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Total Number of Households Waiting to be Routed, Not Yet Receiving Service
columns.description: Households that are in an eligible district and have full building management sign off to start curbside composting sign-up service once their district is added.

columns.name: Percent of Households Waiting to be Routed, Not Yet Receiving Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of households in the district, the percent of households waiting to be routed once their district is added for curbside composting sign-up service.

columns.name: Total Number of Households Not Yet Ready for Service
columns.description: Households that are in an eligible district but are not yet ready to be serviced because DSNY has not received: confirmation from building management, finalized bin set out location, and/or required information to service the address.

columns.name: Percent of Households Not Yet Ready for Service
columns.description: Based on the total number of households in the district, the percent of households not ready for service because DSNY has not received confirmation from building management, finalized bin set out location, and/or required information to service the address.

view.description: Metrics on the status of Curbside Composting sign-up program. Note that Curbside Composting service is currently available to all Queens residents (no sign-up needed), as well as select community boards in Bronx, Brooklyn, and Manhattan. Curbside Composting is expanding to ALL NYC residents. For more information, visit: https://nyc.gov/curbsidecomposting.
